<TITLE> CHT Peace Accord 'not reviewable' by HC </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 13 (bdnews24.com)The High Court has ruled that it can not consider the constitutionality of the Chittagong Hill Tracts Peace Accord. The bench of justices Syed Refaat Ahmed and Moyeenul Islam Chowdhury held that the since the agreement was political in nature - "an accord between belligerents"  it could not be judicially reviewed by the court. The agreement was signed between the government of Bangladesh and the Parbatya Chattagrame Jana Sanghati Samity in 1997. The petitioners who had challenged the legality of the treaty, had argued that the court could consider whether or not the state had acted beyond its authority in executing the accord, notwithstanding the fact the issue had political undertones. The judges started delivering its decision on Monday and is continuing on Tuesday. The court stated on Monday that it would be making a number of "observations" about legislation that has been enacted subsequent to the peace accord. This would include the Regional Council Act 
